Proposed law provides that the adjustment is to be an amount authorized by the system's
actuary with the agreement of the legislative auditor's actuary and supported by the funds
in the system's experience account up to 2% on the first $81,201 of the annual benefit for
eligible retirees and beneficiaries.
Proposed law requires that any cost of proposed law be funded with additional employer
contributions in compliance with present constitution (Art. X, Sec. 29(F)).
Effective June 30, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 11:542.4)
